Commentary: dug in very short, ballooning way over the batsman. Called wide
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 wide

Commentary: fuller, pushed to cover, no run there
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Sikandar Raza, no run

Commentary: short, Raza hops into a pull, up on one leg he is, and gets a good connection too, but equally good fielding on the boundary keeps them to one
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: looks to run a length ball down to third man. Cannot beat point, though
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Sikandar Raza, no run

Commentary: good length, and straightens a bit after pitching. Raza wants to flick it away, but is forced to defend at the last moment
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Sikandar Raza, no run

Commentary: glides this to the right of third man. Mahmudullah looks to attack the ball, one-handed, and ends up misfielding. They get the second quite easily
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Sikandar Raza, 2 runs

Commentary: plays a straighter ball away towards deep backward square leg
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: length, down the leg side, and he misses with a swing
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Madhevere, 1 wide

Commentary: dropped at sweeper cover, but a good effort to get rid of Madhevere. Picks up a length ball, and probably wants to go straight, but ends up skewing it a bit on the off side. The fielder dives forward, but cannot latch on to it
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Madhevere, 2 runs

Commentary: fifty for Madhevere, with a gorgeous straight drive. Uppish, but past the bowler. Win or lose today, this young man has been the biggest gain in these two games for Zimbabwe. Ridden his luck a touch, but shown confidence in his strokeplay and judiciously mixed caution with aggression. His handling of the Bangladesh spinners has been exemplary too
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Madhevere, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish, driven hard towards long-off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: fired straight down, and he's caught in the crease off the back foot. Raza asks him not to review, and there's the breakthrough! Just misreads the line on this, and makes the error of playing back when he could have gone forward. Good ball from Taijul, though
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Madhevere, OUT
Dismissal_text: W Madhevere lbw b Taijul Islam 52 (57b 5x4 0x6) SR: 91.22

Commentary: full, driven back towards the bowler. Bowled around leg and middle
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: driven past the bowler towards long-off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, 1 run

Commentary: cuts one late, and from the stumps almost. Goes through quickly towards short third man, but point gets across to cut this off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, no run

Commentary: presses forward to defend around off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, no run

Commentary: length, around off, driven off the inside of the bat back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: length, lifts this towards long-off, and just clears Tamim, who was three-quarters of the way towards the boundary at long-off
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutumbami, 2 runs

Commentary: smacks this through covers. Should have been stopped at cover, but that was hit with some velocity. Probably also got a bad bounce just around him, did Liton Das. But that's a good shot. Extended well to meet it on a length outside off
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutumbami, FOUR runs

Commentary: looks to run one towards third man, but it goes to point
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: strays down the pads, and he helps it away to the long leg fence. This is excellent batting from Mutumbami, as he keeps the pressure on the bowler
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutumbami, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, angles in, and he taps it towards short mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: length, looks to cut this away, but cannot beat cover
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, no run

Commentary: straighter, and he drives this to the right of the bowler. Easy single on offer
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: length, floated outside off, and he drives this down to long-off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, 1 run

Commentary: length, driven towards long-off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: length, flicks this towards short mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, 1 run

Commentary: length, plays this towards cover and sets off, and they just about make it
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: quick and short, down the leg side, and he gets a bit of bat or glove to that and it fizzes past Rahim through to fine leg. Fifty for Raza!
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Sikandar Raza, FOUR runs

Commentary: another interesting shot. Short, and angling into him, and he goes up off the ground and tonks it to the left of cover for a quick single
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: length, defended towards cover
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: length, back into him from around off, and he is forced to defend
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: length, width on offer, and he goes hard at it, but cannot beat cover. Should have put this away for runs
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: runs this down to third man. Perfect! Just uses Islam's pace against him, and opens the face of the bat enough to run it down
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutumbami, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, and he plays this away towards mid-wicket and takes the quick single on offer
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: down the wicket, chips it in the air towards mid-wicket. Short of the man in the deep
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, 1 run

Commentary: firm drive, moving forward towards wide mid-off, and Afif, the substitute gets across to his left and cuts this off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: defends one straightening into him
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, 1 run

Commentary: length, pushes this towards deep cover. Easy single
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Sikandar Raza, 1 run

Commentary: full ball, and he looks to flick this away, and it's given leg-before, and he reviews immediately! At first glance, it seems to have slid down the leg side, but let's remember the on-field decision is out. It was bowled flat, and fast, and he wasn't able to lay any bat on this. It stays umpire's call, because it was just clipping the top of leg!
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutumbami, OUT
Dismissal_text: R Mutumbami lbw b Taijul Islam 19 (17b 3x4 0x6) SR: 111.76

Commentary: superb shot from Raza! Mortaza is not very quick, and he offers up some width outside off. Raza waits to meet it late, under his eyes, and places it between point and third man
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Sikandar Raza, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, comes forward a touch and plays it away towards deep mid-wicket. They run hard and complete two
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Sikandar Raza, 2 runs

Commentary: moves across, and shuffles this away over short fine leg
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Sikandar Raza, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, too straight, and he has played this past short fine leg. Delightful bit of timing and placement, as he picks two before deep square leg can scurry around and cut this off
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Sikandar Raza, 2 runs

Commentary: slashes this, straight to third man! Raza had picked up 12 off the first four balls, and would have been aiming for six more, but he has timed this a bit too well. A bit short and wide from Mortaza, but at his pace, the batsman is always looking to generate his own speed on the ball. Raza plays a good upper cut, but cannot keep it down, and third man pouches that. That should be game, set and match Bangladesh!
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Sikandar Raza, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sikandar Raza c Mahmudullah b Mashrafe Mortaza 66 (57b 5x4 2x6) SR: 115.78

Commentary: dug in a bit short, and Tiripano fails to make contact with it
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Tiripano, no run

Commentary: length, goes back and slashes hard, but cannot beat cover
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: lofts this over cover, but there's a fielder in the deep now for that shot. A couple of bounces through to him
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: length, and he goes back to defend back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, no run

Commentary: good length, straightens with the angle from around the stumps, and he defends with a forward press
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, no run

Commentary: goes for the reverse sweep, and just about connects before this can crash into his pads. Taijul goes into a half-appeal, but stops. Fielded at short third man
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, no run

Commentary: driven back past the bowler. Uppish, but through to long-off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: length, angles in, and he plays this to short mid-wicket. They take off, and a direct hit, would have had him out at the non-striker's end. As it turns out, he misses!
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: skips down the track, and flogs this through extra cover. Hit with power, and lofted into the gap
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Mutombodzi, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, down the leg side, and he fails to make contact with an intended glance. Called wide, in any case
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Mutombodzi, 1 wide

Commentary: shortens his length seeing the batsman advance. Into his body as he tries to slog it away. They pinch a single, as it must have come off the inside edge
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: flicks a straghter ball towards deep mid-wicket. Just a single for this
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, around off, and he plays this towards cover-point to pick up a single
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: length, straight towards the pads, and he plays this towards mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Mashrafe Mortaza to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: goes for the reverse sweep, and there's a loud appeal for leg before. They choose not to review this, as they run quickly to complete a leg bye
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, 1 leg bye

Commentary: down the wicket, and smacked towards long-on
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: skips down the wicket, and makes it a half-volley outside off. Driven hard towards long-off
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: that's a fine shot! Uses his feet to chip down the wicket, and makes some room on the off side as well. Drives hard, and gets through the cover region. Gave long-off no chance
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutombodzi, FOUR runs

Commentary: holds this back a touch, line along leg, and he whips it towards mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: reverse sweep, but gets only a single to short third man
Commentary_short: Taijul Islam to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: comes down the wicket, and heaves this over long-on. A good shot in the end, because he gave it a proper kitchen-sink treatment. Went quite high, and long enough!
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, SIX runs

Commentary: cracked through covers. Moves away a touch to make room, and then hammers this past mid-off, who's inside the circle
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, FOUR runs

Commentary: looks to pull a shorter ball. Miscued a touch, but still gets it away in the direction of deep mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: smacks this ramrod-straight past the bowler. What a shot! This is such a true wicket, that if you miss the yorker even by a small margin, the batsman can cash in. That's exactly what Mutombodzi does
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, FOUR runs

Commentary: way down the leg side, in trying to tuck the batsman up
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, 1 wide

Commentary: shorter, and slower, and he is through with an attempted biff over point too early
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: slower, short ball again, and he fails to make contact with an attempted run down towards third man. Seemed to pick the length and the pace, but not so much the line of it, just around off
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: goes for a full ball, but ends up offering width. Tiripano has flogged this inside out, over extra cover. Extraordinary!
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Tiripano, SIX runs

Commentary: length, and this is drilled over long-off. What a shot again from DT! Slightly predictable from Islam, and if he misses his length, Tiripano is going to take full toll
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Tiripano, SIX runs

Commentary: short, and he has skewed an intended pull shot. This goes past short fine leg, and teases him on the way through to the boundary!
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Tiripano, FOUR runs

Commentary: that's another delicious shot! Cracked through extra cover and the sweeper gets around to his right and rifles in a throw, but they scamper through for the second
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Tiripano, 2 runs

Commentary: yorker, around off, and he plays this towards point. They settle for the single, though Tirpano wanted a second and took a few steps down for that as well!
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: yorker, driven towards long-on
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: length, and he backs away and tries to knock the leather off this. Only gets it towards deep mid-wicket, but he won't mind getting Tiripano back on strike!
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: backs away, but Al-Amin responds with a yorker on middle stump. Can only drive this towards sweeper cover
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: short, and he swats this away, but cannot get it either side of deep mid-wicket. Lucky for Al-Amin
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: fuller, around off, and he looks to drill this towards cover. Gets it off the outer part of the bat towards deep point
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: fuller length, around off, and he tonks this down towards long-on
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: fuller length, and he swats this hard over cover, and long-off runs around to his left, and does well to hold on to this low to his left. Keeps them down to two, and crucially Mutombodzi to start with the strike
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, 2 runs

Commentary: what a shot! Shafiul looks for the full ball, but cannot nail that yorker, and he shuffles across to access the off side. Lofts this just wide of long-off!
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutombodzi, FOUR runs

Commentary: yorker, and he still advances and plays it away with one hand towards mid-wicket. Slows up around the edge of the circle, and they can come back for two
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutombodzi, 2 runs

Commentary: full toss, around leg stump, and he tries to flog it away on the onside. But he can only hit it deep towards mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: perfect yorker, just around off, and he plays it towards point to pick up the single on offer
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: he's found the gap between mid-wicket and long-on! Shafiul looks to nail the yorker, but it turns out to be a low full toss on leg stump, and he makes room and just smacks it straight through the on side
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutombodzi, FOUR runs

Commentary: makes room, and smacks this inside out, to the left of long-off
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Mutombodzi, 2 runs

Commentary: length, and he has hit this hard, but not too far from long-on. They can only pick a single, as this has travelled quickly
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, 1 run

Commentary: short, and this might be a wide. Yes it is! Mutombodzi was looking to use his feet, and Al-Amin may have shortened his length in response, but it goes too short
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, 1 wide

Commentary: straight shot, but doesn't carry beyond long-on! Brave, brave effort from Mutombodzi comes to an end. Was this a slower ball, perhaps? Because he seemed to get a good hold of it, but it just held up a touch, and ended up being a comfortable catch for the man stationed precisely for that shot. A six there, and the match would really have been on with four balls to go!
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Mutombodzi, OUT
Dismissal_text: CT Mutombodzi c Liton Das b Al-Amin Hossain 34 (21b 5x4 0x6) SR: 161.90

Commentary: Tiripano clears long-on! Skips down the track, and hammers this over long-on. Just short of the sightscreen. This is fabulous from Zimbabwe
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, SIX runs

Commentary: he's got a hold of this! Al-Amin has missed the yorker again, and Tiripano just leans back and gives it everything. Gets it wide, and way high over long-on. Fifty for Tiripano! And an unlikely victory very much in sight now!
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, SIX runs

Commentary: short, and this is a good response from Al-Amin! This is fast, and perhaps goes over the head of DT. He could have had a wide here, but didn't!
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, no run

Commentary: length ball, around off, and he smacks this down to long-off. No fairytale ending, but what a fightback from Zimbabwe!
Commentary_short: Al-Amin Hossain to Tiripano, 1 run
